                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        According
                        to the colophon, the scribe was <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12925ArayaSellaseScribe">ʾArʾāya Śǝllāse</persName>.<date notBefore="1960" notAfter="1961">20th century</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Holy names; names of the king, the metropolitan
                           and the bishop; groups of lines (alternating with black lines) on the
                           incipit page of Texts I-III; groups of lines (alternating with black
                           lines) on the incipit page (one or both columns) of sections of Text I;
                           incipits of miracles; word salām “greetings” in Text III; elements of the
                           punctuation signs and the quire marks; elements of Ethiopic
                           numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#82ra">f. 82ra</locus>
                           <desc type="OwnershipNote">: Ownership note.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="am"/>
                           <note> The note, written in pen, states that the book was
                              bought by ʾato Gabru Gazzāḫāññ. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#84r">f. 84r</locus>
                           <desc type="AcquisitionNote">: Acquisition note.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="am"/>
                           <note> According to the note, ʾAto Gabru Gazzāḫāññ bought
                           the book from ʾalaqā ʾArʾayā Gabra Masqal. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Readings for Text I are indicated by the names of
                              the feasts and other occasions written in the upper margin, in the
                              main hand: fols. 4r, 11v, 15r, 21v, 30v, 35v, 43v, 49r, 53r, 55v, 59r,
                              60v.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
